{
  "texts": [
    "It does not require labels and can achieve very good performance.",
    "As it happened with GAN, it has strong feature extraction and sample generation power (Ren et al. 2022).",
    "As disadvantages, VAE require large amounts of of data, are more theoretically complex than GAN.",
    "It is also difficult to model good loss function, as the resulting marginal likelihood is intractable to compute and optimize, and thus it is learned learned by optimizing a tractable \"evidence lower bound\", obtained using a tunable inference distribution (Zhao et al. 2017).",
    "This can lead to the generation of blurry pictures (Dosovitskiy and Brox 2016)."
  ]
}